The company is going to do a 22 million secondary offering. The company said
Wednesday it would price each share at $12.90/share. 10x the average volume
today and I suspect that much of the trading is due to the secondary
announcement price and arbitrage speculation.

I sold some August $12.5 covered calls on the position I bought 5/20/2009 at
$10.00/share. I think there will be some arbitrage play as the underwriters
have an option to buy more shares at the offering price (up to 30 days after
the issue date). I am betting that when the flood of shares hit the market, the
stock could trade below the secondary offering price of $12.90/share. My
strategy will be to double up on my position and have 1/2 of my position called
away in August. Hopefully, I can also collect the August dividend.

I am not too sure of the dilution to earnings or if the dividend will be cut as
a result of the 22 million share offering. It only represent a 10% increase in
the outstanding shares. The PE continue to be excellent around 10, dividend
payout ratio at 69% well in the good range and a 5.8% dividend yield.

I like the CERC Corp business.

CenterPoint Energy Resources Corp. (CERC Corp. and, together with its
subsidiaries, CERC),is the unregulated component of their business. This
division owns and operates natural gas distribution systems in six states.
Subsidiaries of CERC Corp. own interstate natural gas pipelines and gas
gathering systems and provide various ancillary services. A wholly owned
subsidiary of CERC Corp. offers variable and fixed-price physical natural gas
supplies primarily to commercial and industrial customers and electric and gas
utilities.

CNP should be a good long term hold with growth from their CenterPoint Energy
Resources Corp. This is one I plan to accumulate over the long run.

