Date:6/11/2010 1:57:33 PM
From:E_K_S
Hi Paul -

RE: Becton, Dickinson and Company (BDX)

This was one I followed in the early 90's and owned it for a few years. I never
really looked at it again but now that the health care legislation is a done
deal, this may be one worth building a position in.

What really attracts me to this stock now is their LT debt to earnings payoff
metric. My new Buffet measure is to identify companies with low lt debt
relative to annual earnings: Total lt debt s/b covered by 3 (or 4) years of
annual earnings or less. Based on the YAHOO numbers BDX annual earnings to Long
Term debt coverage is 1.39. In other words, 1.4 years worth of earnings would
pay off their total long term debt. It far exceeds this basic test providing a
high level of safety for the conservative investor.

I would like to pick this up at a PE of 11 or lower but it needs to fall back
to $61.00/share which is another 11% sell off. Not too sure that will happen,
but I will put it on my watch list as this could be a good steady grower once
the economy gets going again.

