From:Madharry
I added another gold stock today which i already own via AAB.to.

This is probably under the realm of too good to be true- The company has mines
in aust. that they bought out of receivership for a pittance. Now they are
producing. They believe that they can produce 100,000 ounces this year and
200,000 ounces next year and increase their proven and indicated resource from
$5 million to $10 million. According to them it costs them $6 to find an ounce
of gold, and about $6-700 to pull it out of the ground. I would say it falls
into the category of a cheap option on the price of gold. They recently did an
offering of around $20 million canadian at i think $1.30. Usually these deal
come with options attached. this didnt. Its called crocodile gold. crk.to. If
they can produce 200,000 ounces its a value stock. otherwise I dont think so
unless gold keeps surging.

The price action on GS is beginning to remind me of the price action on that
fabulous chip company controlled by the potato farmer that was touted by Vinik
a decade ago. Everyday it would be up in the morning and down by the close.
That one ended badly for me.
