Crocodile Gold.

218.6M shares fully diluted @ C$1.22 = $266M market cap (fully diluted)

100,000 oz. production outlooked in 2010. Cost per oz ~$700/oz., so profit
around $550/oz. = $55M. Would this be pre-tax? We don't know how onerous the
Australian proposed mining tax will be when finally implemented. P/e at best
seems to be $266/55 = 4.8.

If 2011 production reaches outlooked/hoped-for 200,000 oz/day and gold price is
as now, then I agree stock at current price would be pretty cheap (p/e under 3,
assuming Australian tax is reasonably low).

